3.24.21  6:08 pm   Why is " I'm a princess" dated to 4/27/2019?

      that's only the audio recording. that's when the audio song was completed

3.24.21  6:04 pm   does it make you feel bad when people assume that your lyrics/videos are random

      yes

3.24.21  5:48 pm   Why did you tell us that we were princesses?

      that's at the end of a video/song all about being a princess. so i just wanted to make sure everyone feels included

3.24.21  5:32 pm   what's the key to making meaningful lyrics

      imagine a scene or situation in your mind, .... then just imagine what it's like to be there, or what might happen next. and sing what happens. Or even if nothing happens, sing what didn't happen

3.24.21  5:29 pm   When did you first conceptualize "I'm a Princess?" A long time ago like "Here Comes the Sun" or recently?

      march 20, 2019

3.24.21  5:05 pm   What is "im a princess about"? 

      listlessness, wishfulness,

3.24.21  4:42 pm   how does one become funny?

      the first step is to call yourself on the phone. it would be interesting to see who answers

3.24.21  4:25 pm   as someone who is trying to pursue music, can you tell me where i should start? or any tips or lessons?

      first ask yourself what you consider 'music'. it must have been something you heard somewhere. If you can figure out what that was and where you heard it, you will be on the right track

3.24.21  3:46 pm   If we go through the window, how can we be sure it's not a door?

      if you had to lift your leg then it's a window

3.24.21  3:13 pm   what is a princess?

      could be you

      how to do that

      simple

      yes

      sing songs of joy

      september, 2016

3.24.21  11:58 am   How are you so good at making songs?

      sometimes the key is to try to do them all wrong

3.24.21  11:15 am   How did you become a great modern philosopher? 

      just trying to get by

3.24.21  10:54 am   Can you use an accordion in a future song?

      sure

3.24.21  10:49 am   I love "im a princess" you threw some real curveballs at us with that one. Did it feel satisfying to finally make the character walk to the beat?

      no, it still looks terrible, even after improving it 900 times. i've forced the entire company into a permanent meeting to discuss this

3.24.21  10:49 am   How did you rhyme "door" with itself 3 times and get away with it?

      ~rhythms~

3.24.21  10:16 am   why do I often feel if I don't do something creative I'm going to lose it?

      i think it's because creativity means very much to you, and you care a lot about it. this is understandible, because creativity is very powerful

3.24.21  10:15 am   Is the guy in "i'm a princess" with the yellow-pink crown-looking thing on his/her head a princess?

      i don't see why not

3.24.21  9:25 am   Hello there Bill! What's your daily routine? Do you write songs and make music every day?

      unfortunately it still takes much longer to produce than to write. but every day i am trying to correct this balance

3.24.21  9:05 am   are peanuts like songs because they have shell that's fibers and then the core peanut that is good but also in a little skin

      i didn't even think of that. i was thinking songs are like peanuts because there's 2 peanuts per peanut, which is difficult to comprehend and even more fun to enjoy

3.24.21  8:43 am   Is there any tips on how to be creative or funny?

      impossible. it can't be done

3.24.21  8:40 am   What is vacationing in the sun.

     me being exasperated and trying to find techniques and processes that work for me

     Is it released?

     yes, it's just that statement

3.24.21  8:36 am   How do you get rid of a weird habit

      you're gonna have to find an even weirder habbit

3.24.21  8:31 am   what will the next song be about?

      finance

3.24.21  8:16 am   I've tried a lot of your recommendations for writing songs and finding inspiration. I've gotten past that part, and I already have a bunch of songs I've made. My problem is that when I make them, it feels almost forced. Taking my own feelings and emotions and using them to make something feels wrong. It's like I'm commercializing my emotions. Am I being irrational? Is this just my self-doubt? Nothing feels right.

      hm, i have an idea. since you said it feels like you are commercializing it ...... have you tried making it is such a way that you think it would NEVER sell

3.24.21  7:40 am   Do you work as a team or solo?

      i work as a team by myself. you may say that doesn't make sense, but welcome to my world

3.24.21  7:26 am   who can be a princess? 

      you or your colleague

3.24.21  7:16 am   do you ever feel overwhelmed by how much there is in the world to learn and experience?

     yes

      if so, how do you cope with this feeling?

     make some plans

3.24.21  7:08 am   What attracted you to make tracks, especially music videos for them.

      to potentially make people feel things

3.24.21  5:53 am   who writes your songs?

      me

3.24.21  4:50 am   do you ever feel creatively trapped by your brand?

      no. my brand does not have any limitations. what traps me is my refusal to remember how easy things could actually be

      a duncess, perhaps

      i was going to say no but now that i think about it yes

      yes

      it probably is possible

would like to ask whats the official name (or the name u mentioned) of this kind of design?

      graphic free title graphics?

3.24.21  2:47 am   what was your inspiration for "I'm a princess?"

      i'm not sure

3.24.21  2:15 am   do you feel there's a significant difference between updating and finishing an old song from like 10 years ago, vs writing a new one and finishing it within a smaller timeframe?

      no

3.24.21  2:14 am   Was the animation in the new video an attempt at combining 2D and 3D?

      yes, somewhat out of necessity, because i already had 1/3 of the video made in a different universe. which i was in no mood to return to

3.24.21  1:50 am   Bill you seem to really have the artist lifestyle figured out. A great unique voice and the people to back you up. You share so much with us all and it is beautiful. My question is this: once I find what I like to do, how do I convince myself to devote all my time into it? I am a very curious person and want to know many things/professions in the world, but my one true calling is storytelling. How can I forget the rest and dive head first with full commitment?

     i guess it just depends on how much you enjoy it, and/or, how bad you want the results

      was F minor but i just raised it to F#min, before doing the vocals

      'proper'
